Singer Waje has taken a swipe at trolls especially those who come at her using grammatically incorrect sentences. According to the 40 -year -old music star the idea of cyber bullying doesn’t actually bother her but the fact that bad grammar is employed during those times is what infuriates her. The mother of one advised her trolls to dazzle her with ‘Shakespearean English’ next time they decide to fling insults at her because, good grammar makes the insults ‘hit the right spot’ Sharing her post, the “Omini Knowest” wrote: “Please don’t insult or cyber bully me if you can’t write correctly. Good grammar dey make insult sweet”, alongside an emoji which depicts one overwhelmed with anger.